<H3> <TI>   Six Minicar Makers Agree To Standardize Parts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1101054594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0511 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1101054594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Osaka, Jan. 11 KYODO -- Six Japanese makers of mini 
vehicles have reached a basic accord to standardize parts for 
their products, one of them firms said Tuesday. 
  Takashi Toyozumi, president of Daihatsu Motor Co., announced 
the agreement at a news conference. 
  The six makers are Daihatsu, Honda Motor Co., Mitsubishi 
Motors Corp., Suzuki Motor Corp., Fuji Heavy Industries Ltd. and 
Mazda Motor Corp. 
  Toyozumi said the agreement is aimed at slashing production 
costs to overcome the long-drawn-out recession. 

</TEXT>

