<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Regional CPP Leaders Arrested in Bacolod City </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1101065894 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1101065894 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Bacolod City, four regional communist leaders 
who have broken with party founder Jose Maria Sison were 
arrested yesterday, the military said. General Pedro Cabuhay, 
commander of the Army's 63rd Infantry Battalion in Negros, said 
those captured included Arturo Tabara, alleged chief of the 
party organization, in charge of all guerrilla and party 
operations in the Visayas. Also arrested were former Roman 
Catholic priest Benjamin Escrupulo, secretary of the regional 
united front committee; Rufino Bianca, secretary of the Negros 
regional party committee, and Tony Lamayo, top guerrilla 
commander of the New People's Army in Negros. 

</TEXT>

