<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cambodia Stance Backed, Western Media Chided </TI></H3>
<H4>   Minister Defends Military, Businessmen </H4>
<F P=102> BK1101084394 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1101084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Speaking to newsmen this morning at Government 
House on the strong reply of the Thai armed forces to Cambodian 
allegations on Thai support for the Khmer Rouge, Foreign 
Minister Squadron Leader Prasong Sunsiri said the reply will not 
cause Thai-Cambodian relations to deteriorate. This is because 
the clarification by the armed forces was straightforward for 
the purpose of achieving nutual understanding. The two 
countries will have to work together to solve their border 
problems. 
  Regarding the criticism by the Cambodian finance minister 
that Thai businessmen are not honest, the foreign minister said 
some businessmen, regardless of their nationalities, are not 
good. Thai businessmen were the first lot to risk their 
investment in Cambodia. Therefore, they should be viewed in a 
broad-minded manner. 

</TEXT>

