<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   France's Chirac Holds Talks With Leaders </TI></H3>
<H4>   Chea Sim on Sihanouk's Health </H4>
<F P=102> BK1101021694 Phnom Penh National Voice of Cambodia Radio 
Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1101021694 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Voice of Cambodia Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning, Samdech Chea Sim, acting head of 
state and chairman of the National Assembly, granted an audience 
to His Excellency [H.E.] Jacques Chirac, former French prime 
minister and mayor of Paris, and his colleagues at Chan Throne 
Hall in the Royal Palace. 
  Samdech Chea Sim welcomed and regarded H.E. Jacques Chirac's 
visit to Cambodia as a sign of further consolidation and 
expansion of Cambodian-French relations and cooperation that 
have existed since time immemorial. Samdech Chea Sim thanked 
the French Government for its role in helping seek peace and 
national reconciliation in Cambodia. He also thanked the Paris 
administration for assistance to the city of Phnom Penh, which 
is facing difficulties. 
  Samdech Chea Sim also informed the guests of His Majesty 
King 
Norodom Sihanouk Varaman's health, saying that his health is 
good, his medical treatment will be complete by the end of 
March, and he will return home at the beginning of April to 
attend the Cambodian traditional new year celebration with all 
Cambodian citizens. 
  H.E. Jacques Chirac stressed the cooperation and assistance 
given by the French Government and the Paris administration to 
Phnom Penh in restoring this capital of the Kingdom of Cambodia, 
which has been ruined by war in the past over two decades. 
  Through Samdech Chea Sim, H.E. Jacques Chirac wished His 
Majesty King Norodom Sihanouk Varaman a quick recovery from his 
illness so that he may return to serve his people. 
  On the same day, H.E. Chhim Siekleng, delegate of the Royal 
Government of Cambodia to Phnom Penh City, also held cordial 
talks with H.E. Jacques Chirac. 
  On that occasion, H.E. Chhim Siekleng thanked the French 
Government and Paris administration for helping to restore the 
city of Phnom Penh. He informed the guest of the difficulties 
facing Phnom Penh and asked the Paris administration to provide 
assistance in rearranging the traffic in Phnom Penh and 
construction equipment and machines for repairing the badly 
damaged roads in the capital. H.E. Chhim Siekleng also asked the 
Paris administration to provide experts for developing Phnom 
Penh and setting up a computer system for the government's 
administrative work. 
  H.E. Jacques Chirac emphasized the goodwill of the French 
Government and Paris to help Cambodia restore the city of Phnom 
Penh. In response to Phnom Penh's requests, H.E. Jacques Chirac 
promised to provide additional equipment, machines, and garbage 
trucks for use in developing and beautifying Phnom Penh. In 
this regard, France will continue helping to establish a clean 
water system and send experts to Cambodia as requested within 
the framework of the association for assistance to the 
Francophone cities. 

</TEXT>

