<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Volume 7 of `Complete Works of Kim Il-song' Published </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0801045994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0432 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0801045994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 8 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of 
Korea Publishing House is publishing Complete Works of Kim 
Il-song which contain immortal classic works of the great 
leader President Kim Il-song systematically in chronological 
order. It has recently brought out its 7th volume. 
  Carried in it are 64 works including historic reports, 
speeches, concluding addresses, statements, talks and 
instructions of President Kim Il-song from January to April 1948. 
  The year 1948 was a historical period when the Korean people 
waged a struggle to consolidate the revolutionary base of the 
northern half of Korea politically, economically and militarily, 
accelerate the building of a prosperous independent and 
sovereign state and reunify the country. 
  The 7th volume consummates the outstanding ideas, theories 
and policies set forth by President Kim Il-song in that period 
to hasten the revolution and construction under the guidance of 
the Workers' Party of Korea with a deep-going scientific insight 
into the requirements of the developing revolution and precious 
successes and experiences attained in the work for their 
realization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

