<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song's New Year Address Reported Abroad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0901082294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0806 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0901082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 9 (KCNA) -- The New Year address 
of the great leader President Kim Il-song has been widely 
reported by foreign media. 
  The Russian paper RABOCHAYA TRIBUNA, the Iranian papers 
RESALAT, KAYHAN INTERNATIONAL and JAHON ISLAM and Radio Iran 
noted that President Kim Il-song in his New Year address showed 
ways for the settlement of the nuclear and reunification issues 
on the Korean peninsula. 
  The Lao News Agency conveyed in detail the words of 
President 
Kim Il-song that the Korean people must thoroughly implement the 
agriculture-first, light industry-first and foreign trade-first 
policies and the DPRK shall consistently adhere to the foreign 
policy of independence, peace and friendship this year. 
  The New Year address was also reported by papers JOURNAL DE 
MADAGASCAR, IMONGO VAOVAO, TRIBUNE and the ANTA News Agency and 
TV of Madagascar, papers MZALENDO, SUNDAY NEWS, THE EXPRESS and 
SHIHATA News Agency and a radio of Tanzania, the Togolese paper 
TOGO-PRESSE, radios and TV of Zimbabwe, the JANA News Agency of 
Libya, a radio and TV of Equatorial Guinea, the U.S. papers 
WASHINGTON POST and NEW YORK TIMES, the British paper DAILY 
AWAZ, the AFP News Agency of France and German-language radios 
of Switzerland from January 1 to 3. 

</TEXT>

