<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Sends 100th Birthday Table </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0801112494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1102 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0801112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 8 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il sent a 100th birthday table to Chon 
Ssanggamae, an old woman residing in Sangchang-ri, Hamju County, 
South Hamgyong Province, on January 6. 
  Upon receiving the birthday table amid blessings of all 
people that day, the old woman and her family, relatives and 
villagers expressed boundless thanks and reverence for the dear 
leader who bestowed deep benevolence on her, caring for the 
birthday of an unknown old woman who has lived an ordinary life. 
  Born into a poor peasant family in a mountainous village in 
Changjin County, South Hamgyong Province, on January 6, 1894, 
she managed to eke out a living by doing farming. She could not 
learn abc, without her proper full name. It was not until Korea 
was liberated in 1945 that she could live a worthy and happy 
life as master of the country. 
  The number of people who enjoy longevity is on a steady 
increase thanks to the popular health policy in the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea. 

</TEXT>

