<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Independence, Peace Said `Consistent Foreign Policy' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0901084094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0823 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0901084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 9 (KCNA) -- Independence, peace 
and friendship is the consistent foreign policy of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea, stresses NODONG SINMUN in 
an article today. 
  The author of the article says: 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song in his New Year 
address declared that the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and the 
DPRK Government would consistently adhere to the foreign policy 
of independence, peace and friendship to meet the requirements 
of the present situation. 
  This year, too, the WPK and the DPRK Government will 
consistently adhere to the foreign policy of independence, peace 
and friendship. 
  The DPRK is a dignified country that regards independence as 
its life and soul. 
  To maintain independence is an invariable position and 
policy 
of the DPRK. The DPRK deems it the basic principle of its 
activity to think and judge all things independently, act in 
accordance with its faith and solve all problems in a 
self-determined manner. 
  The idea of independence in the foreign policy is based on 
the chuche idea, the guiding idea of the DPRK. 
  We never allow others to infringe on our sovereignty, 
interfere in our internal affairs and dominate and control us. 
We also object to violating other country's sovereignty. 
  We will judge and deal with all problems in the 
international 
life with independence as the yardstick and fight on against 
infringement on independence. 
  To avert war and preserve peace is a very urgent problem to 
the Korean people. 
  Out of the sense of obligation to preserve peace in our 
times, we will actively fight to terminate the tension and 
military confrontation on the Korean peninsula, denuclearize 
this part of the world, check and foil the acts of aggression 
and war on the part of the imperialists and reactionaries and 
safeguard peace in Asia and the world. 
  Our people value friendship with the world's people. 
  On the principle of independence we will make positive 
efforts to unite and cooperate with the socialist and nonaligned 
countries and develop good-neighborly and friendly relations 
with the capitalist countries which respect the sovereignty of 
our country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

