<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khmer Rouge Reject Accusation on Thai Army Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1101030894 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in English 0100 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1101030894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by "the National Army of Democratic Kampuchea </F>
spokesman" issued 9 January; place not given -- read by 
announcer] 
  [Text] The National Army of Democratic Kampuchea [NADK]'s 
spokesman rejects the fallacious accusations about the Thai Army 
helping the Khmer Rouge by firing artillery shells against the 
puppet troops. 
  1. Of late, there have been accusations about the Thai Army 
helping the Khmer Rouge by firing artillery shells against 
communist Vietnamese puppet troops. 
  2. The NADK spokesman categorically and totally rejects 
those (?shameless) accusations. 
  3. It is common knowledge that the communist Vietnamese 
puppet troops of the two-headed government has been conducting 
the military offensives against the Democratic Kampuchea party 
and the Cambodian people at the current 16th dry season. Those 
fallacious accusations are part of their bad political scheme 
aimed at concealing their defeats on the battlefield and 
(?against) the national reconciliation policy and the five-point 
guideline of his majesty the king toward national 
reconciliation, peace, and national unity in Cambodia. 
  [Dated] 9 January 1994 

</TEXT>

