  [Excerpt] Hanoi, Jan 11 (AFP) -- Vietnam is prepared to 
hold talks with the United States about "certain problems" 
concerning human rights, a Vietnamese foreign ministry spokesman 
said Tuesday. 
  "Vietnam has told the United States that it is prepared to 
hold talks with the United States and other countries on 
problems of mutual concern, including human rights, on a basis 
of equality, mutual respect and non-interference in the internal 
affairs of each country," he said. [passage omitted] 

