<H3> <TI>   Joint Venture in Expert Services Signed With PRC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1101095894 Vientiane KPL in English 0929 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1101095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, January 11 (KPL) -- A joint venture 
agreement of the Company for Expert Services was signed on 
January 8 between the Lao Government and Lio Yao Petro-chemical 
Company of China. 
  The joint venture was aimed at updating the management and 
business operation of the existing buildings. These buildings 
in the past have been used for business operation by the 
state-run company for expert services. They are located on 
Luang Prabang road, Sithan Neua, Sikhottabong District, 
Vientiane Municipality. 
  This joint business was to serve both local and foreign 
investors. The sides have also agreed to make these buildings 
as a facility for training Lao nationals in housing services. 
The term of the joint venture is 30 years. The Lao side holds 
a share of 30 per cent. Upon termination of the term, all 
assets worth U.S. [$]1,350,000 under the agreement will go to 
the Lao Government. 

</TEXT>

