<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Economic Framework Talks With U.S. </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hata Comments on Talks </H4>
<F P=102> OW1201050794 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 12 
Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1201050794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 11 January </F>
Evening Edition] 
  [Text] At a news conference held after the cabinet meeting 
on 11 January, Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister 
Tsutomu Hata commented on the Japan-U.S. economic framework 
talks, where the deadline to reach agreement on 11 February (the 
Japan-U.S. summit meeting is scheduled on this date) is only a 
month away. He said: "From the point of view of improving the 
Japanese people's quality of life, it is important that Japan 
deals with economic issues voluntarily." He stressed Japan 
should actively promote more transparency in its market by 
deregulation. On the other hand, he also indicated that Japan 
would continue to ask U.S. companies to improve their 
competitiveness and exert more sales efforts, saying: "It is 
necessary not only for the buyers, but also the sellers (the 
United States) to be well-prepared." 

</TEXT>

