<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Economic Framework Talks With U.S. </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Heated Exchange' Expected </H4>
<F P=102> OW1201044094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 12 
Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1201044094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 12 January </F>
Morning Edition] 
  [Text] U.S. Commerce Under Secretary Garten arrived in 
Japan on 11 January to attend the Japan-U.S. vice ministerial 
meeting on automobiles and auto parts, as chief delegate of the 
U.S. side under the Japan-U.S. economic framework talks. The 
U.S. official attended a dinner hosted by Deputy Minister 
Sozaburo Okamatsu of the Ministry of International Trade and 
Industry who is chief delegate of the Japanese side. Both sides 
will hold full-fledged discussions beginning 12 January, and the 
meeting on automobiles and auto parts is set to be held again in 
Washington on 20 January. The two countries are to reach a 
final agreement in a plenary session of the meeting slated for 
late February. 
  Priority has been given to the automobiles and auto parts 
sector, government procurement sector, and insurance sector, and 
the two countries are to draw a conclusion on all sectors by 11 
February when the Japan-U.S. summit talks are to be held. With 
wide differences still remaining between the two countries over 
objective criteria to gauge the degree of market access for 
foreign goods and Japan's plans for the purchase of 
American-made auto parts, however, the two countries are 
expected to have a heated exchange at the vice ministerial 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

