<H3> <TI>   Ulaanbaatar Public Transportation Needs Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1101180894 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1740 GMT 11 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1101180894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 11 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- For 
ensuring a usual activity of the public transport service of the 
Mongolian capital with nearly 600 thousand residents there is 
required more than 490 buses and trolley-buses. According to 
the rough calculations for a partial renovation of the motor 
fleet and purchasing 120 buses it is needed over 3 billion 
tugrik and it is necessary to render urgently proper aid to the 
transport servicemen on the part of appropriate organizations in 
finding such financial resources. 
  Last year in the capital on 21 routes there run about 
160-180 
buses and on 7 routes some 80-85 trolley-buses. The public 
transport service goes on to be the matter of concern of the 
communal service of the Mongolian capital. 

</TEXT>

