<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jasray Reported Set To Restructure Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1201210094 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1938 GMT 12 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1201210094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 12 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- An 
information came from the competent sources near to the 
Mongolian Government that the Mongolian prime minister is going 
within the next few days to make decisive changes in his 
government. According to them, many ministries will be 
abolished, re-organized on the basis of merging with others. 
This project aims at radical changes in the government 
structure, reduction of expenses on maintaining bureaucratic 
apparatus, and the saved means will be directed to the increase 
of wages and pays of state servicemen. 
  According to these sources, this project is actually solved 
it remains only to wait for a decision of the parliament, which 
will consider this project. P. Jasray has presented his project 
at the government sitting, and also to the steering council of 
the ruling Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party. 
  Running across resistance in both cases, the prime minister 
gave to understand that he is going to realize his project 
within the framework of his powers granted by the Constitution. 
  An issue about expediency of re-organization of the 
government, reduction of the number of ministries is raised in 
Mongolia not for the first time. This issue has been raised not 
once by the Mongolian president, the oppositional forces, and 
also by independent economists. 

</TEXT>

