<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Great Hural Reviews Draft Statistics Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1201162394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1520 GMT 12 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1201162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 12. (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
State Great Hural (SGH) session set to consideration of the 
draft law on statistics of Mongolia in the first reading. As it 
was noted at the session of the Mongolian parliament, the task 
of the law on statistics is to define the basic principles of a 
single system of statistical information in Mongolia, regulate 
relations connected with information and statistical research. 
In the draft law reflected are an idea about official and 
unofficial statistics, about official and unofficial 
information, which was not reflected before in the legal acts in 
this respect. According to the draft law, the state and public 
organizations, private economic units and individual citizens of 
the country can carry out official and unofficial statistical 
activity. 
  Discussion of the draft law on statistics continues. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

