<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Kantor's Remarks on Reviving 301 </TI></H3>
<H4>   Remarks Termed `Inappropriate' </H4>
<F P=102> OW1301092894 Tokyo KYODO in English 0912 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1301092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 13 KYODO -- A senior Japanese Foreign 
Ministry official on Thursday [13 January] rapped U.S. Trade 
Representative Mickey Kantor for hinting at reviving the "Super 
301" trade retaliation clause. 
  "There should not be unilateral measures under the framework 
of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade," the official 
said. 
  He criticized Kantor for making "inappropriate" comments in 
the middle of Japan-U.S. trade framework negotiations. 
  Kantor told Japanese reporters in Washington on Wednesday 
that revival of the clause is "an option" for the United States. 

</TEXT>

