<H3> <TI>   Mondale Conveys Inman Wish To Meet Aichi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1301102994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0944 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1301102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 13 KYODO -- Bobby Ray Inman, picked as 
the next U.S. defense secretary to replace Les Aspin, is seeking 
to meet his Japanese counterpart Kazuo Aichi as soon as he 
receives the senate confirmation, U.S. Ambassador Walter 
Mondale said Thursday [13 January]. 
  Mondale conveyed Inman's wish to Aichi when he visited the 
Japanese Defense Agency chief, officials said. 
  Aichi also expressed the hope of meeting with Inman at an 
early stage, the officials said. 
  On Aichi's hope for an early visit to the United States, the 
Defense Agency is now trying to arrange a trip but it could be 
delayed until March or later because of Japanese Diet affairs 
and the compilation of the fiscal 1994 budget, official sources 
said. 
  Last December, President Bill Clinton named Inman, a former 
top Central Intelligence Agency (CIA) official, to succeed Aspin 
as defense secretary. 

