Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 13 KYODO -- The seven parties in Prime 
Minister Morihiro hosokawa's coalition government agreed 
Thursday [13 January] to allow owners of inherited property to 
pay the inheritance tax on them in property itself, party 
officials said. 
  The tax relief measure, agreed upon at a meeting of the 
parties' policymakers, is intended for those who inherited land 
between 1989 and 1991 when land prices skyrocketed amid a real 
estate investment boom and plan to pay the tax in installments, 
the officials said. 
  The coalition parties intend to implement the tax relief 
measure as part of tax reforms for fiscal 1994, they said. 

