<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Receives New U.S. Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1301051994 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1301051994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday in Vientiane, Foreign Affairs Minister 
Somsavat Lengsavat of the Lao People's Democratic Republic 
received Victor L. Tomseth, new ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary of the United States to Laos. 
  The new U.S. envoy paid a visit to the Lao foreign minister 
after he presented a letter of credentials to Laos' President 
Nouhak Phoumsavan on 8 January. 
  The conversation between the guest and the host focused on 
the improvement of efficiency in promoting and expanding the 
relations of friendship, cooperation, and assistance between the 
two countries. 
  Moreover, Somsavat Lengsavat wished the Amrican ambassador 
successes in performing diplomatic duties in Laos. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

