<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA: `U.S. Imperialists' Stage Aerial Exercises </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1301050094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0451 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1301050094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 13 (KCNA) -- The U.S. 
imperialists brought formations of fighter-bombers and 
pursuit-assault planes to the air above Yongwol, Wonju and the 
Tokjok Islet, South Korea, from their base in Japan on January 
11 to stage an exercise of making surprise air raids on 
appointed targets with the support of tanker planes and 
returning nonstop to the base, according to military sources. 
  Synchronizing with the exercise, an Okinawa-based RC-135 
strategic reconnaissance plane flew to the air above the 
Military Demarcation Line area of South Korea and made a flight 
from east to west for aerial espionage on the whole areas of the 
northern half of Korea. 

</TEXT>

