<H3> <TI>   `Famous Works' of Kim Il-song Published </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1201052894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0437 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1201052894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- On the 
Advantages of Socialism in Our Country, a collection of 
works of the great leader President Kim Il-song, was published 
by the Workers' Party of Korea publishing house. 
  Carried in the book in full text or summary are 18 famous 
works of President Kim Il-song including his highly important 
reports and speeches on bringing the advantages of man-centred 
socialism of Korea into full play, which were published in the 
period from April 1955 to April 1992. 
  The book reflects profound ideas on the characteristics and 
essential advantages of socialism in Korea, and the source of 
the might of the socialist system and its invincibility. 
  Comprehensively consummated in the book are concrete tasks 
and ways for bringing the advantages of socialism in Korea into 
full play and outstanding ideas and theories, line and policies 
giving answers to the theoretical and practical questions. 

