<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Great Upswing' in Production Throughout Nation Seen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1201112694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1038 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1201112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- A great upswing has 
been noticed in production in different domains of the national 
economy of Korea in the new year. 
  The Musan mining complex, a major iron headings producer of 
the nation, set itself the goal of producing 1.5 million more 
tons of iron headings this year than last year and has 
overfulfilled daily quotas since the beginning of the new year. 
  The Songjin steel complex topped the first-day's assignments 
of the new year 3.4 percent in steel and 5.1 percent in rolled 
steel. It has since kept a high and steady rate of production. 
  Coal mines in North Hamgyong Province has lifted the daily 
amount of tunneling and coal output more than 20 percent by 
introducing a rational coal cutting method. The Sunchon and 
Anju district coal mining complexes also have overfulfilled 
their daily assignments on all indices since the beginning of 
the year. 
  The east Pyongyang thermal power station generates 80 
percent 
more electricity and produces 2.4 times more hot water for 
central heating on a daily average this year than at the end of 
last year. 
  At the Kaesong textile mill, the daily output of fabrics is 
40 percent up and that of yarn 30 percent up on the daily 
average of last year. 

</TEXT>

