<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report on North's `Nodong No. 1' Missile </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1201235294 Seoul HANGUK ILBO in Korean 13 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK1201235294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul HANGUK ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Yi Chae-mu from Tokyo] </F>
  [Text] An ASAHI SHIMBUN article dispatched from London on 
12 January reported that the British military journal JANE'S 
DEFENSE will carry in its 15 January issue an article reporting 
that the margin of error [ocha] of North Korea's ballistic 
missile "Nodong No. 1," which was test-fired in the East Sea at 
the end of May 1993, is 700 meters and that the missiles will be 
deployed for actual combat around 1996. 

</TEXT>

