<H3> <TI>   Ramos Meets Iranian Minister, Views Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301144794 Tehran IRNA in English 1220 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, Jan 13, IRNA -- Iran's Agriculture 
minister 'Isa Kalantari, currently in Manila, met with President 
Fidel Ramos Thursday and called for direct trade between Iran 
and the Philippines without intervention of a third party. 
  Kalantari also underlined Iran's strategic status in the 
Persian Gulf particularly after the establishment of the newly 
independent Central Asian republics. 
  Ramos welcomed the idea and expressed desire for further 
collaboration between Iran and the Philippines in all areas. He 
said Tehran and Manila could meet each other's needs through 
their recources and facilities. 
  Kalantari also conveyed the greetings of President Akbar 
Hashemi- Rafsanjani to Ramos and briefed him on the agricultural 
developments in Iran. 

</TEXT>

