<H3> <TI>   MILF Ready To Sign Separate Cease-Fires Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1301071794 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1301071794 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tagalog </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Moro Islamic Liberation Front [MILF] is ready to 
sign an agreement with the Philippine Government for the 
implementation of separate cease fires. Government panel member 
Eduardo Ermita made this announcement after receiving hints from 
the MILF headed by Hashem Salamat. Earlier, government panel 
Chairman Manuel Yan disclosed that the government will hold 
separate peace talks with the MILF after the negotiation with 
the MNLF [Moro National Liberation Front] headed by Nur Misuari. 
  [Begin recording, in English, in progress] [Ermita] ... and 
MNLF. 
  [Unidentified reporter] But what about the cease-fire 
processes? 
  [Ermita] When we came from Jakarta, we got word that they 
[MILF] are considering signing a separate cease-fire agreement, 
but we have never been able to confirm that. 
  [Reporter] Will the cease-fire agreement depend on what took 
place during the talks with MNLF? 
  [Ermita] No, it is independent of the MNLF. We are still 
awaiting, lahat eh.... [changes thought], we have not gotten any 
final word from the MILF whether indeed they will sign a 
separate cease-fire agreement with the Philippine Government. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

