<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   SKNDF Publishes Communique After Belgian Visit, Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1201051794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0428 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1201051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- The Seoul-based 
radio Voice of National Salvation published a communique on the 
external activities of the South Korean National Democratic 
Front [SKNDF] (Hanminjon). 
  According to the communique, a delegation of Hanminjon led 
by 
vice-chairman of its Central Committee Hong Chi-yong visited 
Belgium in late November last year and held two rounds of talks 
with a delegation of the Belgian Labour Party led by chairman of 
its Central Committee Ludo Martens. 
  At the talks, Hanminjon expressed support and solidarity for 
the Belgian party's struggle for the interests of the working 
class and other working masses, social progress and world peace 
and noted with appreciation that the Belgian party was striving 
to implement the Pyongyang declaration after signing it. 
  The Belgian Labour Party recognised Hanminjon guided by the 
chuche idea as the organisation representing the desire and will 
of the South Korean people and the patriotic vanguard of the 
movement for a change in South Korea and highly estimated the 
South Korean people's struggle for independence, democracy and 
reunification. It also urged the South Korean authorities to 
stop their acts of dependence, fascism, division and war. 
  The Belgian Labour Party recognised "10-point programme of 
the great unity of the whole nation for the reunification of the 
country" put forward by the great leader President Kim Il-song 
as the best way of removing the danger of catastrophic war and 
tragic division and achieving peace and reunification on the 
Korean peninsula, and expressed support and solidarity for the 
struggle of Hanminjon and the South Korean people to realise the 
10-point programme. 
  Hanminjon and the Belgian Labour Party published a joint 
statement expressing their will to support and closely cooperate 
with each other on the principles of independence, mutual 
respect and non-interference in other's internal affairs and 
further develop inter-party relations through expanded mutual 
contacts. 
  The Hanminjon delegation also visited Switzerland where it 
held talks with a delegation of ohe Workers' Party of 
Switzerland led by President Josef Zisyadis and with former 
mayor of Geneva Roger Dafflon who is Politburo member of the 
Workers' Party of Switzerland, president Edith Ballantyne and 
the general secretary of the International League of Women for 
Peace and Freedom, and others. 

</TEXT>

