<H3> <TI>   Moscow Reported Selling Submarines To DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1401052194 Tokyo TOKYO SHIMBUN in Japanese 12 Jan 94 
Evening Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1401052194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo TOKYO SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By special correspondent A. Portov] </F>
  [Text] Vladivostok, 12 Jan -- A senior officer in the 
Pacific Fleet Command in the Russian Far East revealed on 12 
January that the Pacific Fleet Command plans to export four 
Foxtrot-class submarines -- now deployed at Vladivostok Naval 
Base -- to North Korea and that the contract on their sale has 
already been been signed with North Korea. 
  The contract has been pushed on top secret instructions from 
Navy headquarters in Moscow, and the price remains a secret. 
Officially, North Korea says it will dismantle the submarines 
and use the steel materials therefrom. But a source at Fleet 
Command said North Korea could repair the submarines to create a 
new submarine flotilla or use their parts to repair other 
submarines. 
  The submarines were built in the 1960's. At present, they 
belong to the Submarine Training Brigade and are docked in 
Ussuri Bay. 

</TEXT>

