<F P=101> January </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hosokawa Comments on Outlook for Reform Bills </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1401095894 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 13 Jan 
94 Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1401095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa in a luncheon 
meeting with top leaders of the four major economic 
organizations on 12 January talked about the outlook on the 
House of Councilors' deliberations of the political reform 
bills, and said, "Enactment of the bills on 19 January will be 
difficult." 
  Following the luncheon meeting, an official of the four 
organizations told reporters, "the prime minister said he wants 
to have the bills passed on 19 January and to have the next Diet 
session revise them." But in answer to reporters' question at 
the prime minister's mansion in the evening, Hosokawa denied the 
story, saying: "That is not what I said. They asked me if I 
expected the bills to be passed on 19 January. I told them that 
will probably be difficult." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

